rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be pretty good! The worst of my work and school days are over, and I only need to work two hours tomorrow and I have a short class. I'm going to see my boyfriend soon which is super awesome as I miss him
critical_positive: I think what worked well was that we were both agreeable, humble people. No one was too aggressive or controlling. Also, we had some similar interests in television and movies and some other overlapping traits. My conversation partner was very nice and not too overwhelming so that helped as well.
critical_negative: Maybe I was a bit low energy, maybe my partner wasn't a super great conversationalist, but stuff did just feel off. We had overlapping interests but it was still hard to connect on a deeper level and avoid periods of pausing or space. He did ramble a bit too and I lost interest.

rest_of_day_open: I think it will go okay. I am not in a lot of pain right now and the weather seems to be improving. It seems like some changes in my diet have helped, so hopefully they keep on helping. I am looking forward to more of these chats even if this one wasn't great.
critical_positive: She seemed to mean well, so if I asked her a question she did give an honest answer. We were able to find a few topics of interest that we had in common, so that made for some decent conversation. She did have quite a lot to share if the question was interesting to her.
critical_negative: She seemed very distracted by something else, which made it difficult for the conversation to flow. We didn't really have a lot in common, so it took a while to find things to talk about, and even when we did find some things to talk about, I felt like I had to press her to contribute to the conversation.
